this isn't a bug, but page_idx is a size_t (unsigned integer), so the
condition page_idx % PUNCH_INTERVAL >= 0 is always inherently true and
serves no functional purpose.

> +			    page_idx % PUNCH_INTERVAL < PUNCH_SIZE_FACTOR)
> +				continue;

[ ... ]

