> +	child_failures = atomic_load_explicit(&ctl->child_failures,
> +					      memory_order_acquire);

Does this test ignore the child process's exit status?

If the kernel bug being tested causes the child to crash (for example,
with a SIGSEGV or SIGBUS), waitpid will succeed, but child_failures
will evaluate as 0. This causes the test to incorrectly report a PASS
instead of failing.

Should this inspect the status value using WIFEXITED() or WEXITSTATUS()
to catch child process crashes?

> +	child_verified = atomic_load_explicit(&ctl->child_verified,
> +					      memory_order_acquire);

[ ... ]

