Does ksft_finished() here incorrectly exit with a PASS status?

Since ksft_set_plan() has not been called yet, ksft_plan defaults to 0.
ksft_finished() evaluates whether the plan matches passed + failed +
skipped, which resolves to 0 == 0 + 0 + 0. This artificially inflates
the pass count instead of properly skipping.

Should this use ksft_exit_skip() instead?

> +
