> +		failures = run_iteration();

If run_iteration() exits early due to an error, are the altered THP
settings permanently leaked to the system?

Since run_iteration() calls ksft_exit_fail_msg() on failures like mmap
or fork errors, the process will unconditionally exit via
exit(KSFT_FAIL). This bypasses the thp_restore_settings() call at the
end of main(), permanently leaving the system with altered settings
like shmem_enabled = SHMEM_ADVISE.

